Title
User Pagination with JSONPlaceholder API

Level
1

Time to solve the problem
1.5 hours

Overview
This problem focuses on fetching paginated user data from the JSONPlaceholder API and implementing a pagination system using buttons. The goal is to create a user-friendly interface that allows users to navigate through different pages and view data accordingly.

Detailed Explanation
Topics
Asynchronous Programming
API Fetching
Pagination
Error Handling
Setup Guidelines and Instructions
Use the JSONPlaceholder API (https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users) to fetch user data.
Implement pagination using buttons, where each button corresponds to a specific page, and clicking on a button fetches data for that page.
Display a limited number of users per page (e.g., Page 1, Limit 6).
Problem Statement
Create a web application that fetches user data from the JSONPlaceholder API and implements pagination using buttons. Follow the guidelines below:

Fetch user data for the initial page (Page 1, Limit 6) on page load.
hint: https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users?_page=1&_limit=6
Display the fetched user data in a visually appealing manner.
Implement pagination buttons that allow users to navigate to different pages.
Clicking on a pagination button should fetch and display data for the corresponding page.
Implement proper error handling for API requests.